{"original_position": 8, "diff_hunk": "@@ -0,0 +1,8 @@\n+#!/usr/bin/env bash\n+set -eu\n+\n+BUILD_DIR=$1\n+S3_BUCKET=$2\n+\n+aws s3 rm --recursive \"s3://$S3_BUCKET/\"\n+aws s3 cp --recursive \"$BUILD_DIR\" \"s3://$S3_BUCKET/\" --grants read=uri=http://acs.amazonaws.com/groups/global/AllUsers", "body_text": "It might make more sense to use aws s3 sync --delete \"$BUILD_DIR\" \"s3://$S3_BUCKET/\" --grants read=uri=http://acs.amazonaws.com/groups/global/AllUsers, that way you don't re-copy existing files and only delete those which have been deleted.\nSee: http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/s3/sync.html", "in_reply_to_id": 95707894, "pull_request_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/pulls/409", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/pulls/comments/95708386", "created_at": "2017-01-12T01:09:09Z", "author_association": "NONE", "body": "It might make more sense to use `aws s3 sync --delete \"$BUILD_DIR\" \"s3://$S3_BUCKET/\" --grants read=uri=http://acs.amazonaws.com/groups/global/AllUsers`, that way you don't re-copy existing files and only delete those which have been deleted.\r\n\r\nSee: http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/s3/sync.html", "updated_at": "2017-01-13T00:50:41Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/409#discussion_r95708386", "pull_request_review_id": 16272863, "_links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/pulls/comments/95708386"}, "html": {"href": "https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/409#discussion_r95708386"}, "pull_request": {"href": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/pulls/409"}}, "commit_id": "f15b09c147d37a00bf6972f5b70262ab6081466f", "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/milescrabill/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/milescrabill/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/milescrabill/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/milescrabill", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/milescrabill/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/milescrabill", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/milescrabill/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/4430892?v=4", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/milescrabill/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/milescrabill/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/milescrabill/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "milescrabill", "type": "User", "id": 4430892, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/milescrabill/followers"}, "position": null, "path": "mock-recipe-server/bin/upload.sh", "body_html": "<p>It might make more sense to use <code>aws s3 sync --delete \"$BUILD_DIR\" \"s3://$S3_BUCKET/\" --grants read=uri=http://acs.amazonaws.com/groups/global/AllUsers</code>, that way you don't re-copy existing files and only delete those which have been deleted.</p>\n<p>See: <a href=\"http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/s3/sync.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/s3/sync.html</a></p>", "original_commit_id": "acdde50754a86fc3850b710655ec715e02b41b85", "id": 95708386}